-- Portugal Hotel Revenue Rose 1.5% in July on Foreign Tourists
-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 2012-09-13T10:39:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-13/portugal-hotel-revenue-rose-1-5-in-july-on-foreign-tourists.html
Portugal ’s hotels recorded a 1.5
percent increase in revenue in July from the same month last
year as overnight stays by foreign tourists rose.  Revenue rose to 240 million euros ($310 million) in July,
the Lisbon-based National Statistics Institute said today in an
e-mailed statement. In the first seven months of the year,
revenue fell 2.5 percent to 1 billion euros.  Tourism represents about a tenth of Portugal’s gross
domestic product, according to the  Economy Ministry .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henrique Almeida in Lisbon at 
